@startuml derived-parameter-evaluation
' Requirements: L1-PAR-001
' Source: docs/specs/parameter-processing/L1.md, docs/specs/parameter-processing/L2.md
title Derived Parameter Evaluation from Mission Database Definitions
autonumber

participant "Telemetry Processor" as Proc
participant "Derived Parameter Evaluator" as Derived
database "Mission Database (MDB)" as MDB
database "Parameter Cache" as Cache
participant "Limit Monitor" as LimitMon

[-> Proc : batch of calibrated parameter samples
activate Proc
Proc -> Derived ++ : evaluateDependents(updated parameterRefs)
Derived -> MDB ++ : algorithms triggered by updated inputs
MDB --> Derived -- : algorithm definitions\n(input refs, output parameter, expression)
loop for each triggered algorithm
  Derived -> Cache : read current input values
  Cache --> Derived : input samples
  alt all inputs available and valid
    Derived -> Derived : execute algorithm
    Derived --> Proc : derived sample {value,\ngenerationTime inherited from inputs}
  else missing or invalid input
    Derived --> Proc : derived sample flagged INVALID,\nno value computed
  end
end
deactivate Derived
note over Proc, LimitMon
  L1-PAR-001: derived results are evaluated from
  mission database definitions and re-enter the
  pipeline like any decommutated parameter
end note
Proc -> LimitMon : derived samples enter limit evaluation
[<- Proc : derived results included in publication
deactivate Proc
@enduml
